This paper deals with lung nodule classification using convolutional neural networks and proposes a new method for fine-grained feature analysis and localization. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging and diagnosis, which suggests it could also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI), medical imaging (cs.MED), and information retrieval (cs.IR) categories.
